.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt KSQL_STMT_RESET 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm ksql_stmt_reset
.Nd resets a statement on a database connection
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb ksql
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In stdint.h
.In ksql.h
.Ft "enum ksqlc"
.Fo ksql_stmt_reset
.Fa "struct ksql_stmt *stmt"
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
function resets a statement allocated with
.Xr ksql_stmt_alloc 3 .
.Em Note :
as documented in
.Xr sqlite3_reset 3 ,
this does not unbind statements made with
.Xr ksql_bind_double 3
and friends.
.\" .Sh CONTEXT
.\" For section 9 functions only.
.\" .Sh IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
.\" Not used in OpenBSD.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Returns
.Dv KSQL_OK
on success or another error on failure.
.Em Note :
this does not return the code of
.Xr sqlite3_finalize 3 ,
which itself returns the code of the last step and not the failure of
the resource de-allocation.
